  "texts": [
    "The obtained data demonstrate that the Adam optimizer consistently delivered the best outcomes across all performance measures.",
    "Also, the proposed model was evaluated using binary classification of COVID-19 X-ray images and three classes consisting of coronavirus, normal, and viral pneumonia patients.",
    "The objective of this study was to assess the effectiveness of the Custom-CNN model in examining various relationships, including coronavirus and viral pneumonia, normal and viral pneumonia, and coronavirus and normal, as well as the associations among the three classes of coronavirus, normal, and viral pneumonia.",
    "In the experimental setup, a total of 1,345 chest X-ray images of pneumonia patients, 10,192 normal cases, and 3616 coronavirus-infected chest X-ray images were utilized.",
    "The outcomes were evaluated using various performance metrics such as accuracy, precision, recall/ sensitivity, F1-score, and test loss, as shown in Table 8."
  ]
}